Trying to de-influence my glamorous life on Instagram.
I haven’t slept  properly in 3 months..My baby is my priority 24X7, nothing comes before not even myself..I cry myself to sleep some nights..I cannot sleep when the baby sleeps because that is only time I get to myself..I don’t have a nanny because I don’t have the courage to hand over my baby to someone else..I workout alone and don’t tell my husband about it because my body has zero stamina after giving birth, sometimes I can barely do 10 minutes and I am exhausted..I am self conscious about my c section scar and stretch marks even in-front of my husband..I don’t prioritise my marriage or any other relationship but my baby and I do feel guilty about it..My body does not feel the same and I don’t think it ever will 👏🏼
Honestly I got so many comments during my postpartum regarding my weight..only I know what I went through and how I handled it.
I was told if I loose all that weight I won’t be able to provide nutrition to my baby, someone even said something about liposuction. I understand the fact that being on social media makes you open to all kind of comments and I shouldn’t be bothered about them but sometimes it does bother me.
I gained more than 20 kgs during my pregnancy and the whole time I did wonder would I ever be able to fit into my old clothes, would I ever feel like myself again… I am sure there are so many pregnant ladies who go through the same feeling. Let me share some light on this topic- YES, you can loose the pregnancy weight you just need to work hard on yourself but you are a new person and in my opinion you will not feel like the old you. NO this is not just my luck or my genes. I work hard for myself, I am always on the go.. always working and working out from home if I cannot go to the gym.. maintaining a strict diet, never eating at night which is very hard when you are awake every night breastfeeding.

With all this being said NO loosing weight should not be your first priority, taking care of yourself and your baby should be. Go with your own flow and your body will tell you when’s the right time to start working out 🙌🏼
